Ubuntu Cinnamon 22+:
- Mouse color is kept (Yaru / DMZ-White)
- Theme intensity: Yaru-cinnamon / Yaru-cinnamon-dark

Linux Mint 21.1 Cinnamon+:
- Mouse color: Bibata-Modern-Classic / DMZ-White
- Theme intensity: Mint-Y-Dark-Aqua / Mint-Y-Aqua

Ubuntu 23+:
- Mouse color is kept (Yaru / DMZ-White) gsettings set  org.gnome.desktop.interface cursor-theme 'redglass' # https://askubuntu.com/a/933140
- Theme intensity: Yaru / Yaru-dark gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme "CoolestThemeOnEarth" && gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.wm.preferences theme "CoolestThemeOnEarth" # https://askubuntu.com/a/262946

If Cinnamon is detected: choose between showing desktop on hover or not
If Cinnamon or GNOME are detected: choose between auto-hiding panel or not gsettings set org.gnome.shell.extensions.dash-to-dock dock-fixed false && gsettings set org.gnome.shell.extensions.dash-to-dock autohide true # https://askubuntu.com/a/1005474
